<HL>
   Business Brief -- Pegasus Broadcasting Inc.:
   Closely Held Illinois Firm
   To Be Bought by GE Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
04/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GE
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
</IN>
<LP>
   GE Capital Corp., a financial services unit of General
Electric Co., Fairfield, Conn., said it agreed to acquire
Pegasus Broadcasting Inc., a closely held communications
concern based in Northbrook, Ill. Terms weren't disclosed.
   GE Capital said it has owned preferred stock and warrants
in Pegasus since 1986. Neither GE Capital nor Pegasus would
comment on why GE Capital is taking an equity position in
Pegasus.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pegasus, which said it has annual sales of about $65
million, consists of three independent television stations in
San Juan, Puerto Rico; Augusta, Ga.; and Sacramento, Calif.;
and two radio stations in Helena, Mont. Under the agreement,
GE Capital will acquire the TV stations and Pegasus
shareholders will retain ownership of the two radio stations.
   The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals, and is
expected to close by July. At the closing, a GE Capital
spokeswoman said, the company plans to provide more details
about its interest in Pegasus.
</TEXT>
